data.enText: -ies
of container
the number of things or people that a container or space can hold

data.chText: 那座剧院能容纳2 000名观众。
data.enText: The theatre has a seating capacity of 2 000.
a fuel tank with a capacity of 50 litres
The hall was filled to capacity (= was completely full) .

data.chText: 他们给人山人海的观众表演。
data.enText: They played to a capacity crowd (= one that filled all the space or seats) .
ability
the ability to understand or to do sth
She has an enormous capacity for hard work.

data.chText: 有限的资源正制约着我们开发新产品的能力。
data.enText: Limited resources are restricting our capacity for developing new products.

data.chText: 你那享受生活乐趣的能力
data.enText: your capacity to enjoy life
intellectual capacity
role
the official position or function that sb has

data.chText: 以她作为经理的身份行事
data.enText: acting in her capacity as manager

data.chText: 我们只不过是以顾问身份参与这个项目。
data.enText: We are simply involved in an advisory capacity on the project.
of factory/machine
the quantity that a factory, machine, etc. can produce

data.chText: 这家工厂在开足马力生产。
data.enText: The factory is working at full capacity.
of engine

data.chText: （尤指车辆发动机的）容积，功率
data.enText: the size or power of a piece of equipment, especially the engine of a vehicle

data.chText: 一台功率为1.6升的发动机
data.enText: an engine with a capacity of 1 600 ccs

simple_means.memory_skill: cap 抓 + acity 性质，状态，情况 → 抓住〔事物〕的能力 → 才能

ex.chText: 她有能力经营父亲的企业。
ex.enText: She has the ability to run her father's business.

ex.chText: 他显示出农耕方面的才能。
ex.enText: He shows an ability in/for farming.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，主要用于人，指在智力或体力上能够做某事的实际能力，常后接动词不定式或介词 in/for。

d: 能力，本领，能耐；专门技能

ex.chText: 她具备处理这项工作的能力。
ex.enText: She has the capability to handle the work.

ex.chText: 玛丽有能力成为一名出色的教师。
ex.enText: Mary has the capability of becoming an excellent teacher.

ex.chText: 她认为他做不了同声传译。
ex.enText: In her opinion, simultaneous translation is beyond his capabilities.

synonyms.bx: 尤指完成有难度的事情所需的能力，常后接动词不定式或介词 of，可以复数形式出现。

ex.chText: 他具有操作计算机的能力。
ex.enText: He has a capacity for computers.
The fuel tank has a capacity of 50 litres.

synonyms.bx: 指人理解或做某事的能力，或容器、房间等的容纳能力，常后接介词 of/for。

ex.chText: 你应当尽力保持自己的专业能力。
ex.enText: You should try to maintain your professional competence.

ex.chText: 我们怀疑他教书的能力。
ex.enText: We have doubt about his competence in teaching.

ex.chText: 他在处理这些问题时完全显示出了他的能力。
ex.enText: He demonstrated thorough competence in dealing with these issues.

synonyms.bx: 强调做某事的非凡能力，常后接介词 in。

example: he was employed in the capacity of director
he should be retained in his present capacity at a higher salary
the plant is working at 80 per cent capacity
he had drunk beyond his capacity
among his gifts is his capacity for true altruism

tr: the power to learn or retain knowledge
in law, the ability to understand the facts and significance of your behavior
an electrical phenomenon whereby an electric charge is stored
(computer science) the amount of information (in bytes) that can be stored on a disk drive
example: the capacity of a hard disk drive is usually expressed in megabytes

tr: the amount that can be contained
example: the gas tank has a capacity of 12 gallons

tr: the susceptibility of something to a particular treatment
example: the capability of a metal to be fused

value.def: Your capacity for something is your ability to do it, or the amount of it that you are able to do.

example.ex: Our capacity for giving care, love and attention is limited...
example.tran: 我们能够给予的关怀、关爱和关注是有限的。

example.ex: Her mental capacity and temperament are as remarkable as his.
example.tran: 她的才智和气质和他一样出众。

gramarinfo.label: oft with poss, N <l>for</l> n/-ing, N to-inf

value.def: The capacity of something such as a factory, industry, or region is the quantity of things that it can produce or deliver with the equipment or resources that are available.

example.ex: ...the amount of spare capacity in the economy...
example.tran: 经济中的剩余生产能力

example.ex: Bread factories are working at full capacity...
The region is valued for its coal and vast electricity-generating capacity...
example.tran: 这个地区因其煤炭资源丰富和发电能力巨大而备受重视。

example.ex: Britain must still keep the nuclear and conventional capacity to deal with all conceivable threats.
example.tran: 英国仍须保持核武器和常规武器的生产能力，以应对各种潜在威胁。

value.tran: (工厂、企业、地区的)生产量,生产（或运输）能力

value.def: The capacity of a piece of equipment is its size or power, often measured in particular units.

example.ex: ...an aircraft with a bomb-carrying capacity of 454 kg.
...a feature which gave the vehicles a much greater fuel capacity than other trucks.
example.tran: 使这些车辆的储油量远远超过其他卡车的一个特点

value.def: The capacity of a container is its volume, or the amount of liquid it can hold, measured in units such as litres or gallons.

example.ex: ...the fuel tanks, which had a capacity of 140 litres...
Grease 6 ramekin dishes of 150 ml (5-6 fl oz) capacity.
example.tran: 将6个容量为150毫升(5至6液盎司)的烤盘涂上油。

value.def: The capacity of a building, place, or vehicle is the number of people or things that it can hold. If a place is filled to capacity, it is as full as it can possibly be.

example.ex: Each stadium had a seating capacity of about 50,000...
example.tran: 每个体育场均可容纳5万人左右。

example.ex: Toronto hospital maternity wards were filled to capacity.
example.tran: 多伦多医院的产房都已住满了。

value.tran: (建筑、地方、车辆的)可容纳人数,载客量

value.def: A capacity crowd or audience completely fills a theatre, sports stadium, or other place.

example.ex: A capacity crowd of 76,000 people was at Wembley football stadium for the event.
example.tran: 温布利球场座无虚席，76,000人前来观看这场比赛。

value.tran: 座无虚席的;满场的;挤满的

value.def: If you do something in a particular capacity, you do it as part of a particular job or duty, or because you are representing a particular organization or person.

example.ex: Ms Halliwell visited the Philippines in her capacity as a Special Representative of Unicef...
example.tran: 哈利韦尔女士以联合国儿童基金会特别代表的身份访问了菲律宾。

example.ex: This article is written in a personal capacity...
example.tran: 本文是以个人名义所写。

example.ex: Since 1928, Major Thomas has served the club in many capacities.
example.tran: 自1928年以来,托马斯少校担任过该俱乐部的多个职位。

gramarinfo.label: with supp, <l>in</l> N, oft poss N <l>as</l> n

value.boxu_tran: 不要混淆 capacity，ability 和 capability。capacity 比 ability 更加正式, 表示具有做某事所必需的特质: their capacity for hard work (他们能吃苦耐劳), his capacity to see the other person's point of view (他理解他人观点的能力)。ability 常用来表示能够做好某事: He had remarkable ability as a musician (他拥有杰出的音乐才华), the ability to bear hardship (承受苦难的能力)。capability 表示能完成的工作量及工作质量: a job that was beyond the capability of one man (个人力所不及的工作), the director's ideas of the capability of the actor (导演对那个演员演技的评价)。
value.boxu_usage: Do not confuse capacity with ability and capability. If someone has a particular capacity, a capacity for something, or a capacity to do something, they have the qualities required to do it. Capacity is a more formal word than ability. ...their capacity for hard work. ...his capacity to see the other person's point of view. You often use ability to say that someone can do something well. He had remarkable ability as a musician. ...the ability to bear hardship. A person's capability is the amount of work they can do and how well they can do it. ...a job that was beyond the capability of one man. ...the director's ideas of the capability of the actor.
